&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Specialty Doctor in Clinical Haematology based at the Royal Bournemouth Hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for the appointment to a newly developed position of Specialty Doctor in Clinical Haematology at the Royal Bournemouth Hospital. This is a fixed term post, for six months initially, to provide middle grade cover alongside 3 Specialty Registrars and 2 Core trainees. This post would suit an individual interested in pursuing a career in haematology with the chance to gain experience in managing patients with malignant and non-malignant haematological disorders including those undergoing autologous stem cell transplants, in a friendly progressive department. The appointee will work under the supervision of the eight haematology consultants with exposure to a wide range of subspecialty interests within haematology. The department has a strong clinical research based practice with numerous national non-commercial and commercial clinical trials available to patients to access the latest innovative treatments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‘Interested applicants are welcome to contact the Haematology clinical lead Rachel.Hall@uhd.nhs.uk or David.Allotey@uhd.nhs.uk  for further information or to arrange an informal visit to the department.’&lt;/p&gt;
